---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Divider from '../../components/Divider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Learn More" description="Curated Bitcoin resources — videos, articles, books, and tools for continuing your education.">
  <section class="section-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="page-header reveal">
        <h1>Learn More</h1>
        <p class="section-desc">Curated resources from years of research. Videos, articles, books, and tools to continue your Bitcoin education.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2 class="reveal">Recommended Books</h2>
        <ul class="reveal">
          <li><strong>The Bitcoin Standard</strong> by Saifedean Ammous</li>
          <li><strong>Mastering Bitcoin</strong> by Andreas Antonopoulos</li>
          <li><strong>The Internet of Money</strong> by Andreas Antonopoulos</li>
          <li><strong>Inventing Bitcoin</strong> by Yan Pritzker</li>
          <li><strong>The Blocksize War</strong> by Jonathan Bier</li>
        </ul>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Introduction</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://youtu.be/rc744Z9IjhY" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin: Introduction to the Internet of Money</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>A great introduction by Andreas, touching on what money is, and why the technology of money as information will change the world.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Overview</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l1si5ZWLgy0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Introduction to Bitcoin: what is bitcoin and why does it matter?</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>Andreas explains bitcoin better than anyone, might want to watch it a couple of times.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://dergigi.com/2020/04/27/dear-family-dear-friends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dear Family, Dear Friends: A letter to all of you who still have no bitcoin</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span> <span class="resource-badge">audio</span>
            <p>A simple and comprehensive overview, every newcomer to bitcoin should read this.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A6kJfvuNqtg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin is Punk Rock</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>Andreas explains why bitcoin is disruptive, and why "blockchain" is corporate boardroom friendly bullshit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://medium.com/@MiguelCuneta_21450/its-too-late-nothing-can-stop-the-bitcoin-protocol-738047bb5201" target="_blank" rel="noopener">It's Too Late — Nothing Can Stop The Bitcoin Protocol</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>A great (and short) overview of why bitcoin's mechanics make it inevitable.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K0yESdK22Aw" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guy Swann - Bitcoin An Unstoppable Force</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>A great speech on why bitcoin is eternal.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://quillette.com/2021/02/21/can-governments-stop-bitcoin/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Can Governments Stop Bitcoin?</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>A good introduction to bitcoin as well as a good refutation of many common myths.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nQ0o2Do4n5k" target="_blank" rel="noopener">A Paradigm Shift in Money with American HODL, Preston Pysh, Harry Sudock & Jeff Booth</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>A great speech on why bitcoin and a discussion on the paradigm shift in money that bitcoin represents.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UMK_A0mF8PQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Murad Mahmudov: The Ultimate Bitcoin Argument</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>A great intro to bitcoin.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Investment</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.lynalden.com/invest-in-bitcoin/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">3 Reasons I'm Investing in Bitcoin</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Lyn describes from an unbiased investor's point of view why she's bullish on bitcoin.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Economics</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://vijayboyapati.medium.com/the-bullish-case-for-bitcoin-6ecc8bdecc1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Bullish Case for Bitcoin</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Great overarching economic text, covering the origins of money, benefits of a store of value, characteristics of good monies, common misconceptions and real risks.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.bitrawr.com/the-bitcoin-blackhole-effect" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Bitcoin Black Hole Effect</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Bitcoin's feedback loop in an ever indebted world.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VN2X4bUzgEg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin & A Deflationary World</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>An economic discussion on deflation vs inflation in a bitcoin economy.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iVym9wtopqs&list=PLsy_r4iWMXASWxjkv365JwEcoAXheA9_h&index=15" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin: The Future of Money? | Bitcoiner Book Club | Jordan B. Peterson Podcast</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>A lot of smart people all talking about bitcoin — they cover a lot of ground but it's mostly economic.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Politics</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://bitcoinmagazine.com/culture/bitcoin-is-a-trojan-horse-for-freedom/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin is a Trojan Horse for Freedom</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Why bitcoin's 'number go up' game theory is also a 'freedom go up' tool for establishing human rights.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://bitcoinmagazine.com/culture/bitcoin-seperate-money-state" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin: Our only hope to separate money from state</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Almost like the bitcoin manifesto itself.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Morality</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://bitcoinmagazine.com/culture/check-your-financial-privilege" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Check your financial privilege</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Why bitcoin naysayers miss the bigger picture for bitcoin adoption in countries like Nigeria, Sudan, and Ethiopia.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LgI0liAee4s&t=1s" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Escaping the Global Banking Cartel</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>Andreas explains the problem better than anyone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Mechanics</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://fee.org/articles/decentralization-why-dumb-networks-are-better/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Why Dumb Networks are Better</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Andreas describes why a simple protocol allows for innovation at the edge, encouraging innovation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bBC-nXj3Ng4&list=PLsy_r4iWMXASWxjkv365JwEcoAXheA9_h&index=3" target="_blank" rel="noopener">But how does bitcoin actually work?</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>Another great visual example, but less technical and more overarching.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IaoTtkuY7jM&list=PLsy_r4iWMXASWxjkv365JwEcoAXheA9_h&index=2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Can Quantum Computers Hack Bitcoin?!?</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>How and why bitcoin is quantum computer proof.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://dergigi.com/2021/01/14/bitcoin-is-time/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin is Time</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span> <span class="resource-badge">audio</span>
            <p>How bitcoin is a timechain, and how bitcoin's way of keeping time is integral to its design.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin History</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_txHXuo2ApE" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Unmasking The Creator Of Bitcoin</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>A quick dabble into bitcoin's creator, who they might be, and how this is a potential bitcoin vulnerability. An emotional case for why we are all Satoshi.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://medium.com/interdax/the-symbolic-link-between-the-bitcoin-white-paper-and-halloween-2a967d273ca4" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Symbolic Link Between the Bitcoin White Paper and Halloween</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Satoshi's whitepaper day symbolism compared to the reformation, separation of money and state.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://bitcoinmagazine.com/culture/bitcoin-adam-back-and-digital-cash" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Quest for Digital Cash</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>A great piece on the cypherpunk history of Bitcoin.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://dergigi.com/2021/06/13/bitcoin-is-an-idea/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin Is An Idea</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span> <span class="resource-badge">audio</span>
            <p>Another super detailed lookback into bitcoin's history, and how it was Satoshi's genius to stitch all of these ideas together.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Security</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://notgrubles.medium.com/one-does-not-simply-censor-bitcoin-89dc4a32ba2b" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One does not simply censor bitcoin</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>You're not going to ban Bitcoin, so just give up.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://jimmysong.medium.com/debunking-the-empty-block-attack-10513858b3f8" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Debunking the Empty Block Attack</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Potential threats against bitcoin and how the network would respond.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Finance</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MemwCbp0Y3I&list=PLsy_r4iWMXASWxjkv365JwEcoAXheA9_h&index=5" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Using Bitcoin Loans To Buy Anything</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>Conceptually how taking out a loan against bitcoin works, and why the rich buy everything with credit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Bitcoin Future</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Bitcoin/comments/tuoh5f/im_all_in_bitcoin_the_exponential_age/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">I'M ALL IN: Bitcoin & The Exponential Age</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>A good thread on why bitcoin will play a role in the future.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2020/10/01/self-sovereign-identity-explained/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Self-Sovereign Identity Explained</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>Less about bitcoin, more conceptually how making an NFT of ourselves could revolutionize the future.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Lightning Network</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2021/07/12/the-lightning-network-is-going-to-change-how-you-think-about-bitcoin/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Lightning Network Is Going to Change How You Think About Bitcoin</a> <span class="resource-badge">text</span>
            <p>An in depth look at how bitcoin's layers and programmability could change the world.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://youtu.be/_FwRgGnu0d8" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Future of Bitcoin: Lightning Network</a> <span class="resource-badge">video</span>
            <p>A short documentary clip introducing the lightning network.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Divider />

        <h2 class="reveal">Essential Websites</h2>
        <div class="resource-list reveal">
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://bitcoin.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bitcoin.org</a>
            <p>The original Bitcoin website.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://mempool.space" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mempool.space</a>
            <p>Bitcoin blockchain explorer.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://lopp.net/bitcoin-information.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lopp.net</a>
            <p>Comprehensive Bitcoin information.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="resource-item">
            <a href="https://bitcoin-resources.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bitcoin Resources Library</a>
            <p>If you want to explore on your own, here are some good places to start.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .resource-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .resource-item {
    padding: var(--space-3) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-default);
  }

  .resource-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .resource-item a {
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--gold);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: text-shadow 0.3s ease;
  }

  .resource-item a:hover {
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--gold-glow);
  }

  .resource-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-default);
    padding: 2px 8px;
    margin-left: 6px;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  .resource-item p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
  }
</style>
